truClusterServerModule.name: truClusterServerModule

revisions.description: Rev 1.4 08 Dec 1999 8:30am GMT sun Changed all the CFS counters in truCluCfsClPerfTable to Counter64 type due to the kernel change. Added truCluCfsClPerfTableOctet64 for the SMIv1 compatibility of the updated truCluCfsClPerfTable. Added truCluAliasAddress.
Rev 1.3 1 Apr 1999 8:30am GMT sun Added the SMIv1 support for the Counter64 objects. Removed Overview group and made all objects member-specific.
Rev 1.2 15 Feb 1999 8:30am GMT sun Updated with the initial implementation experience.
Rev 1.1 30 Sept 1998 8:30am GMT sun Incorporated input from the initial version.
Rev 1.0 31 Aug 1998 8:30am GMT sun Initial version of the MIB module, developed to support TruCluster Server Version 5.0

truClusterServerModule.description: This MIB module defines the management objects of COMPAQ's TruCluster Server product.

OctetCounter64.name: OctetCounter64
OctetCounter64.description: Unsigned 64-bit integer as 8 bytes in network byte order ( a format known as big-endian). It expresses a Counter64 quantity in SMIv1.

DrdDeviceType.name: DrdDeviceType
DrdDeviceType.description: The type of DRD (Device Request Dispatcher) devices.

truCluAliasNameTable.name: truCluAliasNameTable
truCluAliasNameTable.description: The table of cluster aliases in a cluster.

truCluAliasNameEntry.name: truCluAliasNameEntry
truCluAliasNameEntry.description: An entry in the cluster name table (truCluAliasNameTable).

truCluAliasIndex.name: truCluAliasIndex
truCluAliasIndex.description: A unique ID of this alias.

truCluAliasName.name: truCluAliasName
truCluAliasName.description: The alias name, may or may not include dotted IP domain name.

truCluAliasFlags.name: truCluAliasFlags
truCluAliasFlags.description: Per-alias flags, reflecting the state of the alias.

truCluAliasMemberTable.name: truCluAliasMemberTable
truCluAliasMemberTable.description: The table of member nodes in an alias.

truCluAliasMemberEntry.name: truCluAliasMemberEntry
truCluAliasMemberEntry.description: An entry in the cluster alias membership table (truCluAliasMemberTable).

truCluAliasMemberName.name: truCluAliasMemberName
truCluAliasMemberName.description: The cluster member name in the alias. This is the same name identified by svrCluMemberName.

truCluAliasMemberFlags.name: truCluAliasMemberFlags
truCluAliasMemberFlags.description: Per-member-per-alias flags, reflecting the member's state within the alias.

truCluAliasMemberSelectWeight.name: truCluAliasMemberSelectWeight
truCluAliasMemberSelectWeight.description: Alias Selection Weight -- an integer indicating in relative terms how many connections this member may accept on behalf of the alias. A member's selection weight divided by the sum of all members' selection weights represents the percentage of alias incoming connections this member can expect to receive over time (other factors being equal). A selection weight of zero (0) means that no incoming connections will be given to this member.

truCluAliasMemberSelectPriority.name: truCluAliasMemberSelectPriority
truCluAliasMemberSelectPriority.description: Alias Selection Priority -- an integer indicating this member's relative primacy in the receipt of new connections for the alias. Incoming connections to the alias will be exclusively distributed among those members with the highest numeric value for selection priority (that is, all connections are distributed among those members with selection priority = 10 if they exist; if no 10's exist, all connections are distributed among those members with selection priority = 9, and so forth. Modifying the selection priority makes it possible for an administrator to determine the failover order for members implementing a particular cluster alias.

truCluAliasMemberRouterPriority.name: truCluAliasMemberRouterPriority
truCluAliasMemberRouterPriority.description: Alias Router Priority -- an integer value to control selection of the designated alias router in a common subnet design.

truCluAliasPerfTable.name: truCluAliasPerfTable
truCluAliasPerfTable.description: The table contains the alias performance counters from a local member's perspective. Some of the terms used are the following: 'forwarded within cluster' and 'received within cluster' refering to tunneled connections ('forwarded' means the local member tunneled the connection or packet to another cluster member; 'received within cluster' means the local member was the tunnelee), 'Data packets' refering to PDUs within a TCP connection, and 'Datagrams' refering to UDP PDUs (PDU stands for 'protocol data unit', also known as packet).

truCluAliasPerfEntry.name: truCluAliasPerfEntry
truCluAliasPerfEntry.description: An entry in the alias performance table (truCluAliasPerfTable).

truCluAliasPerfDataRcvNet.name: truCluAliasPerfDataRcvNet
truCluAliasPerfDataRcvNet.description: Data packets received from the network.

truCluAliasPerfDataFwdClu.name: truCluAliasPerfDataFwdClu
truCluAliasPerfDataFwdClu.description: Data packets forwarded within the cluster.

truCluAliasPerfDataRcvClu.name: truCluAliasPerfDataRcvClu
truCluAliasPerfDataRcvClu.description: Data packets received within the cluster.

truCluAliasPerfTableOctet64.name: truCluAliasPerfTableOctet64
truCluAliasPerfTableOctet64.description: The table contains the alias performance counters from a local member's perspective. Some of the terms used are the following: 'forwarded within cluster' and 'received within cluster' refering to tunneled connections ('forwarded' means the local member tunneled the connection or packet to another cluster member; 'received within cluster' means the local member was the tunnelee), 'Data packets' refering to PDUs within a TCP connection, and 'Datagrams' refering to UDP PDUs (PDU stands for 'protocol data unit', also known as packet). This table is equivalent with the SMIv2 version of the alias performance table (truCluAliasPerfTable). The difference here is that the objects use OCTET STRING instead of Counter64 for SMIv1 compatibility.

truCluAliasPerfEntryOctet64.name: truCluAliasPerfEntryOctet64
truCluAliasPerfEntryOctet64.description: An entry in the alias performance table (truCluAliasPerfTableOctet64.)

truCluAliasPerfDataRcvNetOctet64.name: truCluAliasPerfDataRcvNetOctet64
truCluAliasPerfDataRcvNetOctet64.description: Data packets received from the network.

truCluAliasPerfDataFwdCluOctet64.name: truCluAliasPerfDataFwdCluOctet64
truCluAliasPerfDataFwdCluOctet64.description: Data packets forwarded within the cluster.

truCluAliasPerfDataRcvCluOctet64.name: truCluAliasPerfDataRcvCluOctet64
truCluAliasPerfDataRcvCluOctet64.description: Data packets received within the cluster.

truCluAliasUpdatePeriod.name: truCluAliasUpdatePeriod
truCluAliasUpdatePeriod.description: The number of seconds that must elapse between updates of the alias performance tables (truCluAliasPerfTable and truCluAliasPerfTableOctet64).

truCluAliasLastUpdate.name: truCluAliasLastUpdate
truCluAliasLastUpdate.description: Last update of the alias performance tables (truCluAliasPerfTable and truCluAliasPerfTableOctet64), measured by the value of sysUpTime.

truCluCfsTable.name: truCluCfsTable
truCluCfsTable.description: The table of CFS entries in a cluster. This table excludes any local use file systems, such as procfs (process file system).

truCluCfsEntry.name: truCluCfsEntry
truCluCfsEntry.description: An entry in the CFS entry table (truCluCfsTable).

truCluCfsIndex.name: truCluCfsIndex
truCluCfsIndex.description: A unique index for this file system.

truCluCfsName.name: truCluCfsName
truCluCfsName.description: The name of the file system; for example, cluster_root#root, /dev/rz0c, or goshen:/select.

truCluCfsMountPoint.name: truCluCfsMountPoint
truCluCfsMountPoint.description: The name of the file system's mount point.

truCluCfsServerName.name: truCluCfsServerName
truCluCfsServerName.description: The name of the CFS server node for this file system.

truCluCfsStatus.name: truCluCfsStatus
truCluCfsStatus.description: The status of this file system from a local member's point of view.

truCluCfsClPerfTable.name: truCluCfsClPerfTable
truCluCfsClPerfTable.description: The table contains the CFS client-side performance counters of each cluster file system from a local member's perspective. Each row in the table shows how much the local CFS client has hit a file system with the uncached accesses (real hits).

truCluCfsClPerfEntry.name: truCluCfsClPerfEntry
truCluCfsClPerfEntry.description: An entry in the CFS client performance table (truCluCfsClPerfTable).

truCluCfsClPerfReadOps.name: truCluCfsClPerfReadOps
truCluCfsClPerfReadOps.description: Uncached read operations in 8k blocks (that is, reading a 35k file would count as 5 read operations).

truCluCfsClPerfWriteOps.name: truCluCfsClPerfWriteOps
truCluCfsClPerfWriteOps.description: Write operations (always uncached) in 8k blocks (that is, writing a 42k file would count as 6 write operations).

truCluCfsClPerfReadLinkOps.name: truCluCfsClPerfReadLinkOps
truCluCfsClPerfReadLinkOps.description: Uncached readlink operations. Due to the use of Context Dependent Symbolic Link (CDSL), there are many more symbolic links in a cluster.

truCluCfsClPerfOtherOps.name: truCluCfsClPerfOtherOps
truCluCfsClPerfOtherOps.description: Remaining 'interesting' vnode operations such as create, rmdir, mkdir, remove, rename, open, close, and so forth. All of these operations are uncached by nature - so all hits represent actual filesystem hits (just as the operations above only count actual filesystem hits by ignoring cached hits).

truCluCfsClPerfTableOctet64.name: truCluCfsClPerfTableOctet64
truCluCfsClPerfTableOctet64.description: The table contains the CFS client-side performance counters of each cluster file system from a local member's perspective. Each row in the table shows how much the local CFS client has hit a file system with the uncached accesses (real hits).

truCluCfsClPerfEntryOctet64.name: truCluCfsClPerfEntryOctet64
truCluCfsClPerfEntryOctet64.description: An entry in the CFS client performance table (truCluCfsClPerfTable).

truCluCfsClPerfReadOpsOctet64.name: truCluCfsClPerfReadOpsOctet64
truCluCfsClPerfReadOpsOctet64.description: Uncached read operations in 8k blocks (that is, reading a 35k file would count as 5 read operations).

truCluCfsClPerfWriteOpsOctet64.name: truCluCfsClPerfWriteOpsOctet64
truCluCfsClPerfWriteOpsOctet64.description: Write operations (always uncached) in 8k blocks (that is, writing a 42k file would count as 6 write operations).

truCluCfsClPerfReadLinkOpsOctet64.name: truCluCfsClPerfReadLinkOpsOctet64
truCluCfsClPerfReadLinkOpsOctet64.description: Uncached readlink operations. Due to the use of Context Dependent Symbolic Link (CDSL), there are many more symbolic links in a cluster.

truCluCfsClPerfOtherOpsOctet64.name: truCluCfsClPerfOtherOpsOctet64
truCluCfsClPerfOtherOpsOctet64.description: Remaining 'interesting' vnode operations such as create, rmdir, mkdir, remove, rename, open, close, and so forth. All of these operations are uncached by nature - so all hits represent actual filesystem hits (just as the operations above only count actual filesystem hits by ignoring cached hits).

truCluCfsUpdatePeriod.name: truCluCfsUpdatePeriod
truCluCfsUpdatePeriod.description: The number of seconds that must elapse between updates of the cluster file system performance table (truCluCfsClPerfTable and truCluCfsClPerfTableOctet64).

truCluCfsLastUpdate.name: truCluCfsLastUpdate
truCluCfsLastUpdate.description: Last update of the cluster file system performance table (truCluCfsClPerfTable and truCluCfsClPerfTableOctet64), measured by the value of sysUpTime.

truCluDrdDeviceTable.name: truCluDrdDeviceTable
truCluDrdDeviceTable.description: The table of DRD devices in a cluster.

truCluDrdDeviceEntry.name: truCluDrdDeviceEntry
truCluDrdDeviceEntry.description: An entry in the DRD device table (truCluDrdDeviceTable).

truCluDrdDeviceIndex.name: truCluDrdDeviceIndex
truCluDrdDeviceIndex.description: A unique ID for identifying a DRD device cluster wide, also known as, the device hardware id.

truCluDrdDeviceName.name: truCluDrdDeviceName
truCluDrdDeviceName.description: The name of the DRD device.

truCluDrdDeviceType.name: truCluDrdDeviceType
truCluDrdDeviceType.description: The device type of the DRD device.

truCluDrdDeviceStatus.name: truCluDrdDeviceStatus
truCluDrdDeviceStatus.description: The status of the access node of this DRD device from a local member's perspective.

truCluDrdDeviceAccessNode.name: truCluDrdDeviceAccessNode
truCluDrdDeviceAccessNode.description: The access node which a local member perceives as the DRD server of this device. The access node can be the local member itself. A zero (0) length string is returned if the DRD device status (truCluDrdDeviceStatus) of this device is not OK.

truCluDrdDeviceMibId.name: truCluDrdDeviceMibId
truCluDrdDeviceMibId.description: A MIB ID that is the same value identified by the index of hrDeviceIndex in Host Resources MIB (RFC1514). This ID is member wide, different from truCluDrdDeviceIndex which is cluster wide. This ID is 0 if the device is internal (private) to another member.

truCluDrdServerTable.name: truCluDrdServerTable
truCluDrdServerTable.description: This table illustrates the mapping between the DRD devices and their server nodes in a cluster.

truCluDrdServerEntry.name: truCluDrdServerEntry
truCluDrdServerEntry.description: An entry in the DRD server and device mapping table (truCluDrdServerTable).

truCluDrdServerName.name: truCluDrdServerName
truCluDrdServerName.description: The name of the DRD server node, that is the same member node identified by the value of svrCluMemberName.

truCluDrdSvPerfTable.name: truCluDrdSvPerfTable
truCluDrdSvPerfTable.description: The table contains the performance counters of the DRD devices that are directly served by a local member. A counter in this table is indexed by both a device ID (truCluDrdDeviceIndex) and the ID (svrCluMemberIndex) of a cluster member accessing the device. Each row in the table shows how much a cluster member has accessed the device via the local DRD server.

truCluDrdSvPerfEntry.name: truCluDrdSvPerfEntry
truCluDrdSvPerfEntry.description: An entry in the DRD server performance table (truCluDrdSvPerfTable).

truCluDrdSvPerfReadOps.name: truCluDrdSvPerfReadOps
truCluDrdSvPerfReadOps.description: Read operations the member has issued to the device.

truCluDrdSvPerfWriteOps.name: truCluDrdSvPerfWriteOps
truCluDrdSvPerfWriteOps.description: Write operations the member has issued to the device.

truCluDrdSvPerfReadBytes.name: truCluDrdSvPerfReadBytes
truCluDrdSvPerfReadBytes.description: The number of bytes the member has read from the device.

truCluDrdSvPerfWriteBytes.name: truCluDrdSvPerfWriteBytes
truCluDrdSvPerfWriteBytes.description: The number of bytes the member has written to the device.

truCluDrdSvPerfTableOctet64.name: truCluDrdSvPerfTableOctet64
truCluDrdSvPerfTableOctet64.description: The table contains the performance counters of the DRD devices that are directly served by a local member. A counter in this table is indexed by both a device ID (truCluDrdDeviceIndex) and the ID (svrCluMemberIndex) of a cluster member accessing the device. Each row in the table shows how much a cluster member has accessed the device via the local DRD server. The objects in this table are equivalent to those Counter64 objects in the SMIv2 version of the DRD server performance table (truCluDrdSvPerfTable). The difference here is that they use OCTET STRING for SMIv1 compatibility.

truCluDrdSvPerfEntryOctet64.name: truCluDrdSvPerfEntryOctet64
truCluDrdSvPerfEntryOctet64.description: An entry in the DRD server performance table (truCluDrdSvPerfTableOctet64).

truCluDrdSvPerfReadBytesOctet64.name: truCluDrdSvPerfReadBytesOctet64
truCluDrdSvPerfReadBytesOctet64.description: The number of bytes the member has read from the device.

truCluDrdSvPerfWriteBytesOctet64.name: truCluDrdSvPerfWriteBytesOctet64
truCluDrdSvPerfWriteBytesOctet64.description: The number of bytes the member has written to the device.

truCluDrdUpdatePeriod.name: truCluDrdUpdatePeriod
truCluDrdUpdatePeriod.description: The number of seconds that must elapse between updates of the DRD server performance tables (truCluDrdSvPerfTable and truCluDrdSvPerfTableOctet64).

truCluDrdLastUpdate.name: truCluDrdLastUpdate
truCluDrdLastUpdate.description: Last update of the DRD server performance tables (truCluDrdSvPerfTable and truCluDrdSvPerfTableOctet64), measured by the value of sysUpTime.

truCluCfsServerNew.name: truCluCfsServerNew
truCluCfsServerNew.description: A new CFS server has been elected for a cluster file system. The variables are the following: truCluCfsName - the name of the cluster file system. truCluCfsMountPoint - the mount point of the cluster file system. truCluCfsServerName - the name of the cluster member, as the newly elected CFS server.

truCluDrdDeviceAccessNodeNew.name: truCluDrdDeviceAccessNodeNew
truCluDrdDeviceAccessNodeNew.description: A new access node has been elected for a DRD device. The variables are the following: truCluDrdDeviceName - the name of the device. truCluDrdDeviceAccessNode - the name of the cluster member, as the newly elected access node.

truCluAliasMemberJoined.name: truCluAliasMemberJoined
truCluAliasMemberJoined.description: A cluster member has joined an alias service. The variables are the following: truCluAliasMemberName - the name of the cluster member. truCluAliasName - the name of the alias.

truCluAliasMemberLeft.name: truCluAliasMemberLeft
truCluAliasMemberLeft.description: A cluster member has left an alias service. The variables are the following: truCluAliasMemberName - the name of the cluster member. truCluAliasName - the name of the alias.

truCluAliasGroup.name: truCluAliasGroup
truCluAliasGroup.description: The group of all cluster alias objects.

truCluCfsGroup.name: truCluCfsGroup
truCluCfsGroup.description: The group of all CFS objects.

truCluDrdGroup.name: truCluDrdGroup
truCluDrdGroup.description: The group of all DRD objects.

truCluMibBasicCompliance.name: truCluMibBasicCompliance
truCluMibBasicCompliance.description: This statement describes the requirements for conformance to this MIB module.
